  "response": "Yes, it is a fact that **money laundering is against the law** in virtually every country. Money laundering is the process of making illegally obtained money (from activities such as drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption) appear legitimate by passing it through a series of transactions or financial systems. It is a criminal offense because it enables criminals to profit from illegal activities and undermines the integrity of financial systems.\n\nLaws against money laundering are enforced globally, with countries having their own regulations and participating in international efforts to combat it, such as those led by the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)**. Penalties for money laundering can include severe fines, asset seizures, and imprisonment.",
